If I know Temple fans, they’ll find a way to be upset. However, this steadies the ground the Owls stand on. 

If the big $$ programs turn it around & return to the top of the conference, a P5 conference could show interest. 

For now, the best the Owls can do is win & wait.

In sum, it’s a solid haul for the conference. Some may forecast it as a doomsday, but one of the better outcomes.

Conference stays true to its metro approach, increases in size and fits previous geographic footprint.

The home run is UAB. Good program, growing metro and basketball is on the upswing.

FAU does a great job of keeping conference in FL. School seems aggressive in keeping athletics up to date with latest facilities.

Thoughts on AAC expansion:

AAC building around its Texas home & lands two schools with $ (Rice, North Texas are both ~$40 million athletic budgets, Rice w/ $6 billion endowed & NT has new facilities).

Growing metros (Charlotte, UTSA) w/ young football programs are future bets.
